data.title: This is an above average Starbucks, nothing much to add
data.text: Starbucks has become a commodity and we all have pretty clear expectations, so the main question would a particular cafe turned out to be above or below. This one safely graded above average. There is good service, nice place and all typical Starbucks products present.

data.title: Hey, would you please FILL my cup !!!?
data.text:
What a rip-off it is when you go to a Starbucks and they charge $175 for a cup of java and then fill the cup only 3/4 full!  This is what happened to me today at this location.  When I complained the youing lady said "oh, sorry, some folks want less coffee so they can add cream."
Well, why didn't she ask me before she put any coffee into the cup?  This location is poorly laid out, too, in that right as you go into the place, by the door, is where they hand out the coffee.  To actually order, you have to go around the curb to the cash registers.  Since I was looking where to go when I went in, two "regulars" dashed around me and got in the line first.  This place is a bit of a disappointment.

data.title: Love that coffee
data.text: Enjoyed breakfast there daily as my boys liked to try different pastries and coffee. I was excited they had the Pumpkin Scones as that is my favorite!

data.title: So friendly!
data.text: The cashier was so friendly and chatted about his day, I was soooo tired but since he was so nice I rate this Starbucks very high.

data.title: Excellent service
data.text: This is an excellent location.  The empoyees are very friendly, outgoing and really make an effort to get to know you and go above and beyond with their service to make your experience pleasant, even when they know you are just in town for a few days! Highly recommend them! And the coffee and scones were first class too!

data.title: Simply Good coffee
data.text: There is one reason and one reason alone why I visit Starbucks and that is because I cannot get this good coffee in hotel resturants (which is a shame really). The have a clear focus and I think they are doing a great job.

data.title: Get what you pay for.
data.text: If you want sweet but good tasting coffee, definitely stop by! Prices are a little high, but the coffee, and little snacks are delicious!

data.title: Service yang Baik
data.text: Selain kopinya, memang cabang ini juga memiliki staff yang ramah dan cepat.  Kali ini saya pesan moccha frapucinonya, seperti biasa, enak.

data.title: hummm!!!
data.text: delicioso! como sempre o starbucks e igual em todos os lugares do eua, por isso eu sempre vou e pesso meu capuccino!! voce pode comer bem e pagar pouco isso que e vantagem de viajar para os eua

data.title: Starbucks en California Adventure!!!
data.text: La mejor atencion en todo el parque. La gente extremadamente amable, muy preocupados por el cliente, es una atencion unica considerando que dentro de disney hay locales que dejan mucho que desear. Los felicito jovenes, ademas que el sabor de este cafe es indescriptible!!!!

data.title: L'excellence de bon matin
data.text: J'en avais entendu parlé tellement de fois qu'il fallait que j'y aille au plus vite. Et ça tombait bien car il y en avait un juste à 5 min du motel où on était. J'ai beaucoup aimé leur Frapuccino (désolé si cela n'est orthographié comme il faut), leur chocolat chaud et leur beignet au fromage blanc. A ne pas rater!

data.title: Sehr zu empfehlen...
data.text: Das 4. Starbucks auf unserer Rundreise... Obwohl wir Frühstück und Abendessen im Hotel hatten, machten wir auf dem Rückweg vom Disneyland einen Stop im Starbucks (1200 S. Harbor Blvd.). Es war wahnsinnig voll hier, aber ein großes Lob an die Barista`s. Obwohl die Leute bis zur Tür standen, nahmen Sie sich Zeit für ein paar nette Worte und fragten meine Jungs, wie sie es im Disneyland fanden. Der `Frozen Caramel Frappucino` war genial wie immer...:-). Sehr empfehlenswert!

data.title: Gerne wieder
data.text: Bei unserer Rundreise haben wir die dritte Nacht in Anaheim verbracht. Da unser Hotel keine kostenlose Frühstücksmöglichkeit angeboten haben wir beim Starbucks am 7711 Beach Boulevard (Direkt neben den Movieland Waxmuseums) gefrühstückt. Im einzelstehenden Rundgebäude bekommt man seinen Kaffee und die üblichen Frühstücksangebote von Starbucks. Die Preise sind wie immer einheitlich und günstig für uns. Drinnen sitzen wie immer die vielen "Kaffeetassenhalter" mit ihrem Notebook. Vor dem Starbucks stehen Stühle, Tische und Sonnenschirme. Aufgrund des angenehmen Wetters ist dies sehr angenehm. Das Personal ist wie immer freundlich und nett.
